<p>Few muscle groups transform our physique like a solid pair of biceps. Visible through all forms of clothing, strong and well-defined biceps will have people’s heads turning, and enhance your overall strength.</p>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/bicep-peak-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Building bigger biceps</a> takes more than just a set of average curls. You need to target them from different angles, targeting both bicep heads to create significant growth and definition.</p>



<p>In this article, we will discuss the best dumbbell bicep exercises. We explore correct techniques, expert tips, anatomy, and load recommendations to help you shape an incredible set of arms.</p>



<div class="wp-block-group ft-snippet is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<p class="has-medium-font-size">12 Best Bicep Dumbbell Exercises</p>



<p>These are the twelve best dumbbell bicep exercises for building bigger, thicker biceps in 2024:</p>



<ul>
<li><a href="#dumbbell-concentration-curl">Dumbbell Concentration Curl.</a></li>



<li><a href="#dumbbell-bicep-curl">Dumbbell Bicep Curl.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Reverse-Curl">Dumbbell Reverse Curl.&nbsp;</a></li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Incline-Bicep-Curl">Dumbbell Incline Bicep Curl.&nbsp;</a></li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Lunge-With-Bicep-Curl">Dumbbell Lunge With Bicep Curl.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Alternating-Bicep-Curl">Dumbbell Alternating Bicep Curl.</a></li>



<li><a href="#dumbbell-cross-body-hammer-curl">Dumbbell Cross-Body Hammer Curl.</a></li>



<li><a href="#dumbbell-preacher-curl">Dumbbell Preacher Curl.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Hammer-Curl">Dumbbell Hammer Curl.&nbsp;</a></li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Zottman-Curl">Dumbbell Zottman Curl.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-One-Arm-Zottman-Preacher-Curl">Dumbbell One-Arm Zottman Preacher Curl.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Zottman-Preacher-Curl">Dumbbell Zottman Preacher Curl.&nbsp;</a></li>
</ul>



<p>These exercises utilize different grips and hand positions to target the different parts of the bicep. Performing them together increases volume, promoting great growth.</p>
</div></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">8 Best Dumbbell Bicep Exercises</h2>



<p>These are the eight best dumbbell bicep exercises suitable for all experience levels. Below we list technique guide, load recommendations, and tips to help you get the most out of every rep.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="dumbbell-concentration-curl">Dumbbell Concentration Curl</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-concentration-curl" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell concentration curl</a> has been the go-to exercise to build and shape stronger-looking arms. It involves the same elbow flexion movement as normal bicep curls but uses your thigh to increase isolation.</p>



<p>It targets the biceps short head as the primary mover. The biceps long head, brachialis, brachioradilis, and wrist flexors are the secondary movers.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The internally rotated position of the shoulder places greater emphasis on the biceps long head, developing a bigger bicep peak.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Dumbbell Concentration Curls" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/990003755?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Concentration Curl Guide. <span>Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Grab a dumbbell and sit on the end of a flat bench.</li>



<li>Sitting upright, position your feet shoulder-width apart.</li>



<li>Lean forward and position the dumbbell arm between your legs.</li>



<li>Place the tricep of your dumbbell arm firmly against the inner side of the same thigh.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Your elbow should be just below the thigh, with your elbow extended (straight).</li>



<li>Place your free arm on the other knee for support.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Exhale, flex the elbow and curl the dumbbell up toward your shoulder.</li>



<li>Once the elbow is flexed at shoulder height, pause briefly at the top position. Inhale and gradually lower it back down until the elbow is extended.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Place your free hand on the opposite knee. This will form a solid base, improving your lifting capacity.</li>



<li>Focus on tensing the biceps, and controlling the contracting through the entire movement. This will improve <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26700744/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">mind-muscle connection</a>, enhancing results.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<figure class="wp-block-table table-custom h-title table-border" style="font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-weight:500"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Training Style</p></th><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Sets</p></th><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Reps</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Strength Training</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3–5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">4–6</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Hypertrophy</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3–4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">8–10</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Endurance Training</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3–4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">12–20</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Power Training</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3–5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">1–3 (Explosive)</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps of Dumbbell Concentration Curl</figcaption></figure>
</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="dumbbell-bicep-curl">Dumbbell Bicep Curl</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-bicep-curl" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell bicep curl</a> is a simple and effective way to build bigger biceps. During the curl, the forearms are in the supinated position (palm facing upward), which increases bicep contraction.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The primary movers are your biceps short heads. The long heads, wrist flexors, and wrist extensors work as secondary movers.</p>



<p>The simple movement pattern makes it great for beginners looking to improve their bicep size. The dumbbells also help to work on potential muscular imbalances by working each arm separately.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Dumbbell Bicep Curls" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/978260838?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Bicep Curl Guide. <span>Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Grab a pair of dumbbells. Stand upright, and position your feet shoulder-width apart.</li>



<li>Rotate the dumbbell so that your palms are facing away from the body.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core muscles.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Exhale and curl the dumbbells up toward your shoulders with your elbows tucked to your sides.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Curl until the dumbbells reach shoulder height. Pause briefly at the top position.</li>



<li>Inhale and gradually lower the dumbbells down until they reach the thighs.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Inhale and tense your core before each repetition. This will keep your torso rigid and improve your lifting capacity.</li>



<li>Tense your biceps as you curl the dumbbell. This will improve muscle contraction.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



