<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand.</li>



<li>Keep your arms at your sides, palms facing forward.</li>



<li>Curl one dumbbell upward, squeezing your bicep at the top of the movement.</li>



<li>Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position while curling the other dumbbell.</li>



<li>Alternate between arms for the desired number of repetitions.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your elbows close to your torso to avoid swinging.</li>



<li>Focus on a controlled motion to maximize bicep engagement.</li>



<li>Avoid twisting your torso; keep your core engaged for stability.</li>



<li>Squeeze your biceps at the top of each rep for better muscle activation.</li>



<li>Start with lighter weights to maintain proper form before progressing to heavier loads.</li>
</ul>



