<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="dumbbell-cross-body-hammer-curl">Dumbbell Cross-Body Hammer Curl</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-cross-body-hammer-curl" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell cross-body hammer curl</a> is great for building the biceps and forearms. It utilizes a neutral grip position that better targets the brachialis. When done alongside the other exercises, this improves bicep thickness and appearance.</p>



<p>The primary movers are the biceps short head and the wrist extensors. Secondary movers include the biceps long heads.</p>



<p>Adding these to your existing <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/bicep-isolation-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">bicep workout</a> will increase bicep training volume, which has been shown to <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6303131/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">enhance muscle growth</a>. The neutral grip is also great for improving grip strength which is a <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC10777545/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">vital aspect of health</a> and powerlifting performance.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
