</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Cross-Body Hammer Curl Guide. <span>Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Pick up your dumbbells, and rotate them so your palms face your thighs.</li>



<li>Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart with your hips facing forwards.</li>



<li>Inhale and tense your core.</li>



<li>Rotate the wrist so your palm is facing your body. Exhale and curl the dumbbell up toward the midline of your body. Keep your arm close to your body as you curl.</li>



<li>Once the dumbbell reaches chest height, pause briefly at the top position.</li>



<li>Inhale and, lower it down to the side of your body under control.</li>



<li>Alternate sides for the duration of the set.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips&nbsp;</h4>



<ul>
<li>Ensure that you keep the working elbow close to your body as you curl the dumbbell across it.</li>



<li>Avoid rotating your torso as you perform the movement. Your hips should stay facing forward.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



