<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="dumbbell-preacher-curl">Dumbbell Preacher Curl</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-preacher-curl" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell preacher curl</a> is an isolation exercise that targets the biceps, brachialis, and wrist flexors. Placing the triceps firmly against the padding of the preacher curl helps form a solid base. This allows us to isolate the biceps, increasing muscle activation.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>Preacher curls place the forearms into supinated positions. This emphasizes the bicep short heads and improves overall bicep contraction.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The secondary movers are your biceps long heads, brachialis, and wrist flexors. This makes it one of the great <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/short-head-bicep-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">short-head bicep exercises</a>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Dumbbell Preacher Curl" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/989035524?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Preacher Curl Guide. <span>Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Pick up a pair of dumbbells and sit down on the preacher bench seat.</li>



<li>Lean forward, lift your arms, and position the back of your arms (triceps) against the padding.</li>



<li>Your chest should be in line with the preacher pad. Make sure your feet are flat on the floor.</li>



<li>Lower the dumbbells into the starting position by extending the elbows.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Exhale and curl the dumbbells towards shoulder height.</li>



<li>Pause briefly at the top position. Inhale and lower the dumbbells back to the starting position under control.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips&nbsp;</h4>



<ul>
<li>Avoid fully extending the elbows. Straightening the arm under load in this position can result in bicep tears.</li>



<li>Place the back of your arms firmly against the padding, and tense your core muscles for the duration of the set. This will create a stable base, improving your lifting capacity.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



