<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Zottman-Curl">Dumbbell Zottman Curl</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-zottman-curl" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell Zottman curl</a> is an incredible biceps-building exercise that requires increased forearm activation. It combines the elbow flexion movement with wrist rotation to target your forearm and wrist muscles.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The primary movers are the biceps short heads and biceps long heads. Secondary movers include the brachialis, brachioradialis, wrist flexors, and wrist extensors.</p>



<p>Adding the dumbbell Zottman curl to your workout is excellent for increasing your bicep and forearm training volume. This increases stimulus, creating greater growth. The rotation provides a bigger grip challenge, increasing grip strength.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
