<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-One-Arm-Zottman-Preacher-Curl">Dumbbell One-Arm Zottman Preacher Curl</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-one-arm-zottman-preacher-curl" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell one-arm Zottman preacher curl</a> adds an element of isolation for a more focused muscle contraction. Placing the back of the arm against the preacher bench improves stability and reduces potential shoulder involvement. This increases intensity, enhancing the growth of the primary movers.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The biceps short heads and biceps long heads are the primary movers. The secondary movers are the brachialis, brachioradialis, wrist flexors, and wrist extensors. The curl combines the motion of the standard bicep curl with a wrist rotation. This takes the biceps and forearms through a full range of motion.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
