</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell One-Arm Zottman Preacher Curl Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Adjust the incline bench to a 45-degree angle.</li>



<li>Pick up a dumbbell, and stand at the back of the bench, directly behind the back pad.</li>



<li>Set your feet up in a split stance. The leg of the working arm should be inside the bench leg rests. Position your working arm on the bench.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. With your palm facing upward, straighten your elbow, while keeping your upper arm firmly placed on the bench.</li>



<li>Exhale and curl the dumbbell toward the shoulder. Once the elbow is bent at approximately 90 degrees, pause.</li>



<li>Rotate the dumbbell so that your palm faces the floor.</li>



<li>Inhale and gradually lower the dumbbell until your arm is straight.</li>



<li>Pause, then rotate the forearm so your palm faces upward again.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips&nbsp;</h4>



<ul>
<li>Do not fully straighten the arm. This can strain the biceps and elbows, which can lead to injury.</li>



<li>Keep your tricep firmly pressed against the bench. This will create a stable base and improve your capacity to isolate the biceps and forearms.</li>
</ul>



