<li>Place your feet flat on the floor. Keep your chest up with your head facing forward.</li>



<li>Straighten your arms and gradually lower the dumbbells to the starting position. You should be using an underhand (palms facing up) grip.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Exhale and curl the dumbbells toward shoulder height.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Pause at the top. Rotate your wrists so your palms are now facing towards the floor.</li>



<li>Inhale as you gradually lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Rotate your wrists so your palms are facing up again.</li>
