<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Anatomy Of The Biceps</h2>



<p>The <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK519538/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">biceps brachii</a> occupies the front of the upper arm. It consists of two heads — the short head (inner side) and the long head (outside). Its primary functions are to flex the elbow and stabilize shoulder movement.</p>


